import React, { useState } from 'react' const AddUser = () => { // const[firstName,setFirstName]= useState("") // const[lastName,setLastName]= useState("") // const[email,setEmail]= useState("") // const[password,setPassword]= useState("") // const[roadNo,setRoadNo]= useState("") // const[houseNo,setHouseNo]= useState("") // const[city,setCity]= useState("") // const[district,setDistrict]= useState("") // const[confirmPassword,setConfirmPassword]= useState("") const[inputs,setInputs]= useState({ firstName:"", lastName:"", email:"", password:"", roadNo:"", houseNo:"", city:"", district:"", confirmPassword:"" }) const {firstName,lastName,email,password,roadNo,houseNo,city,district,confirmPassword}=inputs const setFirstName=(e)=>setInputs({...inputs,firstName:e.target.value}) const setLastName=(e)=>setInputs({...inputs,lastName:e.target.value}) const setEmail=(e)=>setInputs({...inputs,email:e.target.value}) const setPassword=(e)=>setInputs({...inputs,password:e.target.value}) const setRoadNo=(e)=>setInputs({...inputs,roadNo:e.target.value}) const setHouseNo=(e)=>setInputs({...inputs,houseNo:e.target.value}) const setCity=(e)=>setInputs({...inputs,city:e.target.value}) const setDistrict=(e)=>setInputs({...inputs,district:e.target.value}) const setConfirmPassword=(e)=>setInputs({...inputs,confirmPassword:e.target.value}) return (
setFirstName(e.target.value)} className="form-control" type="text" />
setLastName(e.target.value)} className="form-control" type="text" />
setEmail(e.target.value)} className="form-control" type="email" />
setPassword(e.target.value)} className="form-control" type="password" />
confirmPassword(e.target.value)} className="form-control" type="password" />
}
setRoadNo(e.target.value)} className="form-control" type="text" />
setHouseNo(e.target.value)} className="form-control" type="text" />
setCity(e.target.value)} className="form-control" type="text" />
setDistrict(e.target.value)} className="form-control" type="text" />
) } export default AddUser
